rComments: Test are tough, Stay away from this course. Don't be fooled by the course description. You better know everything about the subject before taking this course.  Talk about a subject A during class but you end up being testes on Y,Z,W. Also you will not get a chance to drop the course because the midterm is after the  droping deadline.

No clear marking scheme and marks hard. Since it is a "graduate level course", you are expected to know everything before you even enroll the course. He will not teach you anything because you should know everything The exams test you on everything you can think of around the course subject even though he did not go through any of them.

This prof is ridiculous; test are extremely technical. He does not teach anything at all in class. Off topic within 2 mins of lecture. Highly suggest you avoid this prof at a graduate level unless you are highly knowledgeable in the field. Midterm average on open book test for graduate level  51%. Stay away, stay very far away!!! Rate should be 0

The webpage has a minimal setting of 15, but it should actually be 05. He doesn't teach, expects us to know everything, no textbook, no PowerPoint, off tangent every 2 min, teach you A test you on Z. Midterm average was 51% for a graduate level class where students clearly know how to study, but there was nothing to study with.
